native bush
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:indigenous forest
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1950 still a popular term, though in technical and semitechnical Forest Service publications it has been replaced by the unpromising indigenous bush or forest (cf indigenous - rather than native  timber, tree etc distinct from exotic).
